Package: inflately
Type: Package
Title: Inflating Costs to Present Value (PV) Using Different Source Rates
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Nathan Green <nathan.greenf@imperial.ac.uk>
Maintainer: Nathan Green <nathan.greenf@imperial.ac.uk>
Description: Inflating costs to present value (PV) is a routine step in
    cost-effectiveness analyses. Further, there are different inflation
    rates depending on the type of cost to be inflated.
Depends:
    R (>= 3.5.0),
    utils
